            <INFO_MODIFICATIONS>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The Battle of Britain Memorial Flight (BBMF) project delivery team requires additional services over a limited period of 1 year in order to maintain BBMF Aircraft Airworthiness and meet its mandated regulatory requirements as set out by the military aviation authority.</P>
                  <P>The original contract is being modified via a 12 months extension with an increase in financial sanction of 273 511 GBP.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <ADDITIONAL_NEED>
                  <P>A change in contractor would require training with BBMF’s unique technology, safety management systems and platform integrity. Duplicating cost and time incurred on the original contract, and resulting in significant effort from MOD personnel who would otherwise be carrying out activities critical to platform safety and would render the first 6 months of a 12 months contract ineffective. The loss of knowledge and suitably qualified and empowered personnel would impact on aircraft airworthiness.</P>
               </ADDITIONAL_NEED>
